# Lichess as Reference

When in doubt about UI/UX decisions, chess behavior, or feature design, follow how Lichess (lichess.org) does it.

This applies to:
- Board appearance and piece styling
- Move animations, highlights, and visual feedback
- Check/checkmate indicators
- Promotion dialogs
- Game controls (resign, draw, undo)
- Puzzle trainer flow
- Time controls and clock display
- Sound effects and notifications
